11:58.410 --> 12:00.947
Lot of people thought
you got away with murder.

12:00.980 --> 12:02.208
Really? I had no idea.

12:02.250 --> 12:04.810
Certainly not why
I changed my name.

12:07.160 --> 12:10.129
Look, my dad was not a nice man,

12:10.160 --> 12:11.980
okay?

12:12.030 --> 12:13.827
He was cruel,
and he beat me.

12:13.860 --> 12:15.851
So when he died,
I didn't weep or wail

12:15.900 --> 12:17.891
or do any of those things

12:17.930 --> 12:20.160
teenage girls apparently do
when their dad dies.

12:20.200 --> 12:22.862
So everyone assumed
that I killed him.

12:22.910 --> 12:25.265
Let's talk about Titus Delancey.

12:25.310 --> 12:27.403
Okay.
Are you aware he was poisoned?

12:27.440 --> 12:28.976
Yes, and to answer
your next question,

12:29.010 --> 12:30.204
no, I didn't kill him.

12:30.250 --> 12:31.945
Then why are you
sounding so defensive?

12:31.980 --> 12:33.914
Because I'm being interrogated
by the police.

12:33.950 --> 12:36.168
So I feel like being defensive
is sort of a natural reaction.

12:36.220 --> 12:38.347
You don't find it
the least bit coincidental

12:38.390 --> 12:41.780
that he was killed
with the exact poison

12:41.820 --> 12:43.959
that killed your father?

12:43.990 --> 12:45.321
No, I find it
extremely coincidental,

12:45.360 --> 12:46.952
but I didn't do it.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.353
Any idea who did?

12:48.400 --> 12:50.220
I have no idea, okay?

12:50.270 --> 12:51.794
I'm the nanny.

12:51.830 --> 12:53.331
He and I weren't close.

12:53.370 --> 12:55.065
We didn't spend a lot
of time together.

12:55.100 --> 12:57.364
Where were you last night?

12:57.410 --> 12:58.832
(sighs)

12:58.870 --> 13:00.337
Home alone.

13:00.380 --> 13:02.371
That's a lousy alibi, Abigail.

13:02.410 --> 13:03.843
Yeah, well, if I knew
I needed one,

13:03.880 --> 13:05.973
I would've
invited somebody over.

13:06.010 --> 13:08.149
I keep to myself.

13:08.180 --> 13:10.080
I have ever since
the trial.

13:10.120 --> 13:12.987
Lost every friend you ever had,
didn't you?

13:13.020 --> 13:16.478
The ones who thought
I was guilty were afraid of me.

13:16.520 --> 13:19.250
And the ones who
knew I was innocent

13:19.290 --> 13:20.826
couldn't be around me

13:20.860 --> 13:23.397
without being in every paper
in the country.

13:23.430 --> 13:25.569
The media ruined my life,

13:25.600 --> 13:28.433
and now it's about to happen
all over again,

13:28.470 --> 13:30.131
thanks to you.

13:30.170 --> 13:32.229
After I ran away,

13:32.270 --> 13:33.305
I got plastic surgery.

13:33.340 --> 13:34.409
No one has recognized me

13:34.440 --> 13:36.101
in 19 years.

13:36.140 --> 13:38.005
How did you do it?

13:38.050 --> 13:39.847
Your voice.

13:39.880 --> 13:42.314
I just recognized it
from the media coverage.

13:42.350 --> 13:44.341
(sighs)

13:46.590 --> 13:48.114
Look,

13:48.160 --> 13:50.287
I know you can't prove

13:50.330 --> 13:53.128
that I had anything to do
with Mr. Delancey's death.

13:53.160 --> 13:55.299
If you could've, you would've
arrested me back at the house.

13:55.330 --> 13:58.163
So, if you don't have
any more questions,

13:58.200 --> 14:00.031
I would like to leave please.

14:00.070 --> 14:01.935
I've spent enough of my life

14:01.970 --> 14:04.063
being accused
of things I didn't do.

14:11.410 --> 14:13.571
Doesn't feel right,
letting her go.

14:13.620 --> 14:15.315
I mean, you talk
about a solid suspect.

14:15.350 --> 14:17.045
She was right; we don't
have enough evidence

14:17.090 --> 14:19.046
to hold her yet.

14:19.090 --> 14:21.650
I don't believe she did it.

14:21.690 --> 14:23.282
You're the one
who pointed her out.

14:23.330 --> 14:24.979
Her presence
at the Delancey home

14:25.030 --> 14:26.383
was too remarkable to ignore,

14:26.430 --> 14:28.455
but her haptics suggest
she's telling the truth.

14:28.500 --> 14:31.060
Titus Delancey was killed
with nitroglycerine.

14:31.100 --> 14:33.091
So was her dad;
that can't be a coincidence.

14:33.140 --> 14:34.596
I agree,

14:34.640 --> 14:37.006
but I think the similarities
are qUIte deliberate,

14:37.040 --> 14:38.928
and I think
whoever poisoned Mr. Delancey

14:38.970 --> 14:40.403
intends to frame Ms. Spencer.

14:40.440 --> 14:42.305
That would mean
the killer knew who she was.

14:42.340 --> 14:45.343
She said no one had
recognized her in 19 years.

14:45.380 --> 14:47.348
As far as she knows.

14:51.390 --> 14:53.153
So you want to
tell me how you knew

14:53.190 --> 14:54.612
about her tattoo?

14:54.660 --> 14:56.548
Beg your pardon?

14:56.590 --> 14:58.455
Abigail's tattoo.

14:58.490 --> 15:00.253
When you recognized
her today,

15:00.300 --> 15:02.097
you said it was
because of her voice,

15:02.130 --> 15:05.190
but I think it was
something more than that.

15:05.230 --> 15:07.460
You fixated on the tattoo
on her wrist.

15:07.500 --> 15:10.037
At first I thought
you remembered it

15:10.070 --> 15:12.971
from a picture that was taken
during her trial, but then,

15:13.010 --> 15:14.204
when I looked back at coverage,

15:14.240 --> 15:16.174
Abigail did not have a tattoo.

15:16.210 --> 15:17.700
So how could you
have recognized it?

15:17.750 --> 15:19.604
Impressive, Watson.

15:19.650 --> 15:21.242
Quite impressive.

15:21.280 --> 15:23.111
You know,

15:23.150 --> 15:25.084
the truth is
that Abigail Spencer and I

15:25.120 --> 15:26.985
are old acquaintances,

15:27.020 --> 15:29.079
after a fashion.

15:29.120 --> 15:31.623
By the time I was 15,

15:31.660 --> 15:34.220
I was fascinated by murder
and all things...

15:34.260 --> 15:35.488
criminal.

15:35.530 --> 15:37.191
Abigail was so beautiful,

15:37.230 --> 15:39.266
and her father's fortune so vast

15:39.300 --> 15:42.337
that the UK tabloids actually
deigned to cover the case.

15:42.370 --> 15:44.133
Over time, they lost interest.

15:44.170 --> 15:45.728
I did not.

15:45.770 --> 15:48.204
I became fascinated
by the question of her guilt.

15:48.240 --> 15:50.743
So I wrote to her.

15:50.780 --> 15:53.749
A letter comprised
of very direct questions

15:53.780 --> 15:57.147
about her life
and her father's death.

15:57.190 --> 15:58.418
Hmm.

15:58.450 --> 15:59.678
So she wrote back.

15:59.720 --> 16:02.484
Yeah, we corresponded
throughout the trial

16:02.520 --> 16:04.624
and for a while afterwards.

16:04.660 --> 16:06.423
In one of her later missives,

16:06.460 --> 16:08.428
she mentioned that she wanted
to get a tattoo

16:08.460 --> 16:10.325
of a phoenix on her wrist.

16:10.370 --> 16:12.326
A symbol of her rebirth

16:14.070 --> 16:16.163
Why didn't she recognize
your name today?

16:16.200 --> 16:18.703
I mean, Sherlock Holmes
is pretty hard to forget.

16:18.740 --> 16:20.230
In my teenage years,

16:20.280 --> 16:23.044
I was a lot less self-assured
than I am today.

16:23.080 --> 16:25.173
I yearned
for a more typical name.

16:25.210 --> 16:27.041
So for a while,
I attempted to be known

16:27.080 --> 16:28.741
as Sean Holmes.

16:28.780 --> 16:30.179
Didn't stick,

16:30.220 --> 16:32.188
but Sean
and Abigail's correspondence

16:32.220 --> 16:35.519
became a very real window
into the criminal mind.

16:35.560 --> 16:37.323
Are you saying
that she confessed

16:37.360 --> 16:38.725
to killing her father to you?

16:38.760 --> 16:41.194
She never
directly addressed the issue.

16:41.230 --> 16:44.119
Without knowing,
she revealed details,

16:44.170 --> 16:46.195
which I believe,
filled in the holes

16:46.230 --> 16:47.538
in the case against her.

16:47.570 --> 16:49.128
As for her relationship
with her father,

16:49.170 --> 16:52.139
well, she shared some things

16:52.170 --> 16:54.400
which must have been
quite humiliating for her.

16:54.440 --> 16:55.805
She left me in little doubt

16:55.840 --> 16:57.808
that he was, indeed,
physically abusive

16:57.850 --> 17:01.741
and that she was responsible
for his death.

17:01.780 --> 17:03.611
Wow.

17:03.650 --> 17:05.618
Sounds like
she really opened up to you.

17:05.650 --> 17:07.584
She was an excellent
research subject.

17:07.620 --> 17:09.383
She was very forthcoming,

17:09.420 --> 17:12.082
attributable primarily
to her isolation at the time,

17:12.130 --> 17:15.793
and my promise that
whatever she shared with me

17:15.830 --> 17:17.422
would be kept
in the strictest confidence.

17:17.470 --> 17:19.461
That doesn't sound
like you at all.

17:19.500 --> 17:21.434
I mean, not telling anyone

17:21.470 --> 17:23.267
that you'd figured out
that she was guilty?

17:23.310 --> 17:24.800
Trial was over.

17:24.840 --> 17:27.536
Double jeopardy protected her
from a second,

17:27.580 --> 17:30.105
and I was quite confident
that although she had killed,

17:30.150 --> 17:32.277
she was not a killer.

17:32.310 --> 17:34.210
She posed no threat
to anyone other than her father.

17:34.250 --> 17:36.775
Titus Delancey
might disagree.

17:36.820 --> 17:39.186
Well, as I told you, I don't
believe Abigail's responsible.

17:39.220 --> 17:41.780
You think she's being framed,
but how can you be so sure?

17:41.820 --> 17:44.584
You are relying on a judgment
you made when you were 15.

17:44.630 --> 17:46.120
Well, when I made it
is irrelevant.

17:46.160 --> 17:47.696
What matters is I was right.

17:47.730 --> 17:49.425
I believe

17:49.460 --> 17:51.428
that when I have identified
the person

17:51.470 --> 17:54.359
who has uncovered Abigail's
secret, we'll have our killer.

17:54.400 --> 17:56.436
(indistinct chatter)

17:56.470 --> 17:57.767
(doorbell rings)

17:57.810 --> 18:00.608
(gasps)

18:00.640 --> 18:02.471
I don't know who let you in,

18:02.510 --> 18:04.569
but you're not allowed
to be up here.

18:04.610 --> 18:06.271
My name is Sherlock Holmes.

18:06.310 --> 18:08.244
I work with the police.

18:08.280 --> 18:09.542
We met yesterday.

18:09.580 --> 18:11.116
Well, unless you have a warrant,

18:11.150 --> 18:12.640
I don't want to talk
to you, either.

18:12.690 --> 18:14.157
You used
to know me.

18:14.190 --> 18:16.249
By another name.

18:16.290 --> 18:18.383
Sean Holmes.

18:18.430 --> 18:20.455
(gasps)

18:20.500 --> 18:23.492
I don't understand.

18:23.530 --> 18:25.361
You could have told me
yesterday.

18:25.400 --> 18:28.494
Well, I confess to being
a little thrown when I saw you.

18:28.540 --> 18:30.735
Also, I didn't know how

18:30.770 --> 18:34.501
to explain our relationship
to my colleagues.

18:36.840 --> 18:38.603
I never thought
this would happen.

18:38.650 --> 18:40.208
(sighs)

18:40.250 --> 18:41.774
I never thought
I would meet you.

18:41.820 --> 18:43.685
(sighs)
I used

18:43.720 --> 18:45.915
to look forward to receiving
your letters so much.

18:45.950 --> 18:47.611
And I yours.

18:47.660 --> 18:50.788
Peri fired me.

18:50.830 --> 18:53.526
I didn't even get to say
good-bye to Graham or Zack.

18:53.560 --> 18:56.449
I'm sure you've seen my friends
who are outside the building.

18:57.970 --> 18:59.494
You could have pulled me aside
yesterday.

18:59.530 --> 19:01.168
You could have kept this
between us.

19:02.300 --> 19:04.905
I'm sorry... for any turmoil

19:04.940 --> 19:07.170
I have caused you.

19:07.210 --> 19:09.531
(sniffles)

19:09.580 --> 19:12.799
I supposed
I should apologize, too.

19:14.580 --> 19:17.219
I'm the one who stopped writing.

19:17.250 --> 19:19.616
I'm the one who disappeared
without saying good-bye.

19:19.650 --> 19:21.914
I understood.

19:21.960 --> 19:25.179
You needed
to leave Abigail behind.

19:25.230 --> 19:27.721
So the phoenix might rise.

19:31.700 --> 19:35.488
I came here today because
I-I don't believe

19:35.540 --> 19:37.508
that you killed
Titus Delancey.

