22:30.850 --> 22:32.909
most of the evening.
You and Dr. Malone

22:32.950 --> 22:35.373
having an affair?
Because if that's
the case, you didn't

22:35.420 --> 22:36.773
need to bring
a lawyer with you.

22:36.820 --> 22:38.048
That's not it.

22:38.090 --> 22:39.648
As you would
eventually discover,

22:39.690 --> 22:41.112
Dr. Malone has a prior arrest

22:41.160 --> 22:43.788
for illegal distribution
of prescription meds.

22:43.830 --> 22:47.527
My client is happy
to testify against Dr. Malone

22:47.560 --> 22:49.528
if you'll agree not to bring
charges against her

22:49.560 --> 22:50.720
in the death of her husband.

22:50.770 --> 22:52.795
Well, if your client
has a solid alibi,

22:52.830 --> 22:54.536
what would we
charge her with?

22:54.570 --> 22:57.937
We'd like to avoid
an attempted murder charge.

22:57.970 --> 23:01.474
Mrs. Delancey, what medication

23:01.510 --> 23:03.808
did you purchase
from Dr. Malone?

23:03.850 --> 23:06.569
Nitroglycerin.

23:06.610 --> 23:08.976
Which you were planning
to use to kill your husband.

23:09.020 --> 23:13.684
I was... considering it.

23:13.720 --> 23:17.759
I figured if I went through
with it, I could call in

23:17.790 --> 23:20.588
an anonymous tip,
tell the police about
who Anne really was,

23:20.630 --> 23:21.949
and she'd get the blame.

23:22.000 --> 23:23.695
But to be clear...

23:23.730 --> 23:26.824
it was just something
I thought about.

23:26.870 --> 23:31.000
I don't think I ever could
have actually hurt Titus.

23:31.040 --> 23:32.860
So your client's
statement is

23:32.910 --> 23:34.673
that she couldn't
have killed her husband

23:34.710 --> 23:37.907
because she was too busy
planning to kill her husband?

23:47.990 --> 23:49.514
First time in my career

23:49.560 --> 23:51.187
someone's alibi for murder
has been

23:51.230 --> 23:53.619
that they were busy planning
the same murder.

23:53.660 --> 23:55.890
If it weren't so frustrating,

23:55.930 --> 23:56.897
it would be interesting.

23:56.930 --> 23:57.965
Yeah, well, it worked out
for Peri Delancey.

23:58.000 --> 24:01.163
Six months on drug charges
beats life in prison.

24:01.200 --> 24:04.533
Why did you add a photograph
of the two Delancey kids?

24:04.570 --> 24:05.764
Only one of them

24:05.810 --> 24:07.903
is a suspect.

24:07.940 --> 24:10.647
A short while ago,
I obtained a copy

24:10.680 --> 24:12.944
of Mr. Delancey's estate plan.

24:12.980 --> 24:15.744
Now that he's dead, a large part
of his fortune goes into trusts

24:15.780 --> 24:18.681
for his sons;
millions of dollars

24:18.720 --> 24:21.086
they will be able
to access as soon
as they're 18.

24:21.120 --> 24:23.088
That's only one year away
for Graham.

24:23.120 --> 24:25.588
Also, the young man no longer
has an alibi.

24:25.630 --> 24:27.120
Peri Delancey has admitted

24:27.160 --> 24:29.048
she wasn't actually with
the boys that evening.

24:29.100 --> 24:31.227
So Graham himself could
easily have snuck back home.

24:31.270 --> 24:32.965
There's no evidence that he knew

24:33.000 --> 24:34.934
about Abigail's history
as a poisoner.

24:34.970 --> 24:38.531
The very topic I plan to discuss
when I confront him tomorrow.

24:38.570 --> 24:40.879
Isn't tomorrow Titus Delancey's
memorial service?

24:40.910 --> 24:42.730
Precisely.

24:42.780 --> 24:44.202
You heard what
you just said, right?

24:44.250 --> 24:46.002
You're planning
to harass a teenage boy

24:46.050 --> 24:48.109
while he's mourning
his father?

24:48.150 --> 24:50.687
If he's the poisoner, he won't
really be mourning, will he?

24:50.720 --> 24:52.813
You know, the police think
Abigail is their best suspect?

24:52.850 --> 24:56.809
I do. As I told you,
I do not share their suspicions.

24:56.860 --> 24:58.680
That's because you were
in love with her.

24:58.730 --> 24:59.879
What?!
Back when you were

24:59.930 --> 25:02.023
a kid when you were writing her,
you fell in love with her.

25:02.060 --> 25:03.721
You spent almost three hours
at her house today.

25:03.770 --> 25:05.692
And in spite of what happened
with Peri Delancey,

25:05.730 --> 25:08.096
no one thinks she's being framed
except for you.

25:12.070 --> 25:13.833
I was quite young

25:13.880 --> 25:17.179
when my father shipped me off
to boarding school, right?

25:17.210 --> 25:20.919
I struggled. I was different
from my classmates.

25:20.950 --> 25:24.078
I was, uh, well, I was more
intelligent. H was brash.

25:24.120 --> 25:26.645
So they tormented me
mercilessly.

25:26.690 --> 25:29.318
Yes, I remember you saying once
that you had been bullied,

25:29.360 --> 25:31.624
_ but I wasn't sure
if you were telling the truth.

25:31.660 --> 25:33.924
It happened. I overcame it.

25:33.960 --> 25:36.224
It was a different
time back then.

25:36.260 --> 25:38.592
There was no such thing
as harassment via text

25:38.630 --> 25:40.666
or circulation of cruel
cell phone Videos.

25:40.700 --> 25:43.931
No, my bullies had one tool
at their disposal: violence.

25:43.970 --> 25:45.938
So I was beaten.

25:45.970 --> 25:49.178
Fairly savagely
and with great frequency.

25:49.210 --> 25:51.644
That's when you started
writing Abigail.
Mm.

25:51.680 --> 25:53.910
She was being abused
and so were you.

25:53.950 --> 25:55.178
Uh, I meant what I said before.

25:55.220 --> 25:57.586
My-my interest in her
was academic.

25:57.620 --> 26:00.612
She was to be a subject
of study, nothing more.

26:02.220 --> 26:04.927
I confess,
as our correspondence continued,

26:04.960 --> 26:08.794
I grew more anticipatory
of her letters.

26:08.830 --> 26:11.719
They were a welcome distraction
from my life.

26:11.770 --> 26:14.591
They were an oasis from school.

26:14.640 --> 26:16.267
Well, it certainly sounds like
you had feelings for her.

26:16.300 --> 26:18.268
Perhaps but...

26:18.310 --> 26:20.232
nothing so mundane as love.

26:22.980 --> 26:25.175
I was adrift back then.
I had-had no purpose.

26:25.210 --> 26:28.043
My so-called peers made me feel
that that might always be...

26:28.080 --> 26:29.638
the case.

26:29.680 --> 26:33.684
Abigail, she gave me a gift.

26:33.720 --> 26:37.929
A view inside a mind capable
of murder.

26:37.960 --> 26:40.349
So she was your first.

26:40.390 --> 26:43.769
Killer, yeah.

26:43.800 --> 26:46.792
Without intending
to, she...

26:46.830 --> 26:49.367
she helped me understand
who I was and...

26:49.400 --> 26:52.938
and what I might do
with my life.

26:54.940 --> 26:57.875
You never told her you thought
she was guilty, did you?

26:59.110 --> 27:01.840
I didn't want her
to stop writing.

27:01.880 --> 27:03.643
I didn't think

27:03.690 --> 27:05.112
she'd be a threat
to anyone else.

27:05.150 --> 27:07.243
There was no point.

27:07.290 --> 27:09.850
I get that.

27:09.890 --> 27:12.029
But if she killed
Titus Delancey,

27:12.060 --> 27:13.721
then she's got...
Then she'll be
handed over

27:13.760 --> 27:15.398
to the police
and she'll be punished.

27:15.430 --> 27:20.163
But for now, I'd like to try
to help her.

27:25.440 --> 27:27.135
WATSON:
Graham.

27:27.170 --> 27:29.172
Hi.

27:29.210 --> 27:31.269
I'm Joan. This is Sherlock.
We met the other day.

27:31.310 --> 27:33.175
Yeah, you're the people
that took Anne away.

27:33.210 --> 27:36.316
Of course I remember you.

27:36.350 --> 27:39.410
How are you and, uh,
Zack holding up?

27:39.450 --> 27:41.452
The past two days,
our dad was murdered,

27:41.490 --> 27:44.755
our nanny was accused of the
crime and our stepmom confessed

27:44.790 --> 27:46.428
to thinking
about killing him.

27:46.460 --> 27:48.826
We're great.

27:48.860 --> 27:51.988
I know
it's a lot.

27:53.070 --> 27:55.334
Zack's pretty mixed up.

27:55.370 --> 27:57.190
Especially about Peri.

27:57.240 --> 27:59.435
He liked her a lot more
than I did.

27:59.470 --> 28:01.438
But our Aunt Susan's here now.

28:01.480 --> 28:03.698
She's-she's great.
She's taking care of us.

28:05.410 --> 28:07.446
Were you aware
that your father's will

28:07.480 --> 28:10.711
leaves you and your brother
a substantial amount of money?

28:10.750 --> 28:13.287
Yeah, I guess. Never
really thought about it.

28:13.320 --> 28:15.811
Why?
Financial gain
has motivated

28:15.860 --> 28:17.851
many a murderous endeavor.

28:21.030 --> 28:23.225
Wait a second, are you saying
you think I killed my dad?

28:23.260 --> 28:25.228
Your stepmother's confession
has weakened

28:25.270 --> 28:26.498
your alibi.

28:26.530 --> 28:28.760
We know that she
left your home

28:28.800 --> 28:30.939
in Bedford the night
of the murder.

28:30.970 --> 28:33.063
Your brother was in_ his
room watching teleVI5ion.

28:33.110 --> 28:34.737
It would've been easy
enough for you...

28:34.780 --> 28:37.499
No! No way.

28:37.540 --> 28:40.373
Everyone knows it was Anne or
Abigail, whatever her name is.

28:40.410 --> 28:42.275
She did it.
It's all in the papers.

28:42.320 --> 28:43.787
Do you have any notion as to why

28:43.820 --> 28:45.447
she would've murdered
your... father?

28:45.490 --> 28:47.481
Unlike you,
she had nothing to gain.

28:47.520 --> 28:49.317
No, but she and my dad
had issues.

28:49.360 --> 28:51.225
We haven't heard that
from anyone else.

28:51.260 --> 28:54.229
All I know is they got in a
big argument just last week.

28:54.260 --> 28:55.750
And I can prove it.

28:55.800 --> 28:57.495
Zack had learned
this new parkour move

28:57.530 --> 28:59.498
and he wanted me to film him.
Then I realized my dad was

28:59.530 --> 29:03.830
going off on Abigail
in the hallway. I got
it all on my phone.

29:10.110 --> 29:11.975
(indistinct arguing)

29:17.850 --> 29:19.386
Where did you get this?

29:19.420 --> 29:21.285
Graham.

29:21.320 --> 29:22.958
Police technicians

29:22.990 --> 29:24.821
were able to enhance
the audio

29:24.860 --> 29:27.124
so we could discern some
of what Titus was saying.

29:27.160 --> 29:29.128
As far as we can make out,

29:29.160 --> 29:31.264
someone had attempted
to access his tablet

29:31.300 --> 29:33.837
without his permission
and he was upset about it.

29:33.870 --> 29:36.361
He was crazy that day.

29:36.400 --> 29:38.368
He thought I'd tried to
steal it or something.

29:38.410 --> 29:40.230
Had you?
No.

29:40.270 --> 29:42.534
Of course not.

29:42.580 --> 29:44.275
You should know that,
as we speak,

29:44.310 --> 29:46.847
the police are attempting
to locate his tablet

29:46.880 --> 29:48.370
at the Delancey home.

29:48.420 --> 29:50.274
They're hopeful
that it will shed some light

29:50.320 --> 29:52.538
on the investigation.
Why would it?

29:52.590 --> 29:56.151
It's been theorized that...
Titus uncovered your secret,

29:56.190 --> 29:58.283
that he had evidence
of it on his tablet

29:58.330 --> 30:00.355
and his aim was using that
against you.

30:02.060 --> 30:04.597
You're a_ beautiful woman.
He was in a bad marriage.

30:04.630 --> 30:08.293
Perhaps he prevailed on you
for other services.

30:08.340 --> 30:10.296
That's not true.

30:10.340 --> 30:13.002
Mm? It was rather a heated
argument. And frankly, I'm...

30:13.040 --> 30:15.429
curious as to why you never
mentioned it before.

30:15.480 --> 30:17.300
I forgot about
it. He...

30:17.340 --> 30:20.468
Titus apologized. He
said he o-overreacted.

30:20.510 --> 30:23.115
It wasn't
a big deal.

30:26.620 --> 30:29.350
You-you understand
that I'm trying to help you,

30:29.390 --> 30:32.188
and I can't do that
unless you're completely
honest with me.

30:32.230 --> 30:33.322
Of course I'm being honest.

30:33.360 --> 30:34.918
I've always been
honest with you.

30:34.960 --> 30:37.929
Well, we both know
that's not true.

30:37.970 --> 30:40.530
What are you
talking about?

30:42.670 --> 30:47.039
I know that you poisoned
your father, Abigail.

30:47.070 --> 30:49.504
Why are you saying that?

30:49.540 --> 30:52.100
You said that
you believed me.

30:52.150 --> 30:54.072
I avoided the subject
whenever possible.

30:54.120 --> 30:55.644
Not all the time.

30:55.680 --> 30:57.341
You said you
believed me.

30:57.380 --> 31:00.087
In a letter dated
September '91,

31:00.120 --> 31:02.259
you mentioned the passing
of a beloved neighbor,

31:02.290 --> 31:04.258
heart condition.
You often ran errands for her.

31:04.290 --> 31:06.588
She was the unwitting supplier
of the nitroglycerin

31:06.630 --> 31:09.622
that you used to poison
your father, was she not?

31:11.630 --> 31:14.394
January '92, you wrote
that you were with a classmate

31:14.440 --> 31:16.192
at the time of his death, but...

31:16.240 --> 31:18.333
at trial you said
that you went to the store.

31:18.370 --> 31:21.168
Shall I go on? Because I can.

31:24.450 --> 31:26.543
I know the truth, Abigail.

31:26.580 --> 31:29.242
I've known for 22 years.

31:31.990 --> 31:34.083
Get out.

31:35.120 --> 31:37.156
Abigail...
Get out.

31:40.630 --> 31:43.019
(sighs)

31:49.470 --> 31:52.166
Hey. The guys
are striking out here.

31:52.210 --> 31:54.428
I mean, there's no sign
of Delancey's tablet.

31:54.480 --> 31:55.504
What about you?

31:55.540 --> 31:57.098
I don't know.

31:57.140 --> 31:58.641
I might have something.

31:58.680 --> 32:02.116
Looks like someone tried
to pry this drawer open.

32:02.150 --> 32:03.640
Other than you.
(chuckles)

32:03.680 --> 32:05.386
Give me some credit.
I used to be a surgeon.

32:05.420 --> 32:09.311
I would never leave
a mess_ like this.
(clicks)

32:12.530 --> 32:15.693
Well, why would someone
lock an empty drawer?

32:15.730 --> 32:17.425
Habit.

32:20.170 --> 32:21.535
(sighs)

32:21.570 --> 32:23.299
(drawer shuts)

32:23.340 --> 32:26.559
Well, we know from the video
that he was angry

32:26.610 --> 32:28.305
because he thought that Abigail

32:28.340 --> 32:30.171
had gotten ahold
of his tablet.

32:30.210 --> 32:32.701
Right? So if this
is where he kept it

32:32.750 --> 32:34.445
and if there was
sen5itive information

32:34.480 --> 32:36.277
about her past on it,

32:36.320 --> 32:38.413
maybe these scratches
made him suspicious.

32:38.450 --> 32:40.589
You know, my ex used to keep
her tablet in a case

32:40.620 --> 32:42.315
that looked just like a book.

32:42.360 --> 32:44.555
Maybe it's on one
of these shelves.

32:44.590 --> 32:47.286
(sighs)

32:59.770 --> 33:02.079
There are_five air vents
in this room.

33:02.110 --> 33:04.476
And the capital of Michigan
is Lansing.

33:04.510 --> 33:06.705
You know you're starting
to sound like your partner.

33:08.180 --> 33:10.068
(knocking)

33:10.120 --> 33:11.109
Well, don't you think it's odd?

33:11.150 --> 33:12.219
I mean...

33:12.250 --> 33:14.389
the room is not that big, right?

33:14.420 --> 33:16.615
There's usually one vent
for intake, and then...

33:16.660 --> 33:17.786
(knocking)

33:17.820 --> 33:20.357
...maybe one or two
to blow cold air.

33:20.390 --> 33:21.391
(knocking)

33:22.430 --> 33:23.749
Five is definitely overkill.

33:23.800 --> 33:24.789
How do you know that?

33:24.830 --> 33:27.390
My uncle was a contractor.

33:31.210 --> 33:33.405
Hey, check this out.

33:33.440 --> 33:34.771
This isn't a vent.

33:34.810 --> 33:37.335
It's just supposed
to look like one.

33:46.590 --> 33:47.648
(phone rings)

33:47.690 --> 33:50.056
Watson, I'm on route.

33:50.090 --> 33:52.058
I will be
at the Delancey home shortly.

33:52.090 --> 33:53.728
You can turn around.
We found the tablet.

33:53.760 --> 33:55.648
Was there evidence
he knew about Abigail?

33:55.700 --> 33:58.419
No.

33:58.470 --> 34:00.119
But I think you were
right last night.

34:00.170 --> 34:02.138
I think maybe Graham
did kill his father.

34:02.170 --> 34:03.535
What did you find?

34:03.570 --> 34:07.233
Videos of Titus with Graham.

34:07.270 --> 34:09.773
He was sexually abusing him.

34:14.350 --> 34:15.339
(door opens)

34:15.380 --> 34:17.541
Ms. Moore?
Tom Gregson.

34:17.580 --> 34:20.083
Appreciate you bringing
your nephew in to talk to us.

34:20.120 --> 34:21.758
Marsha Whitman, I
represent the family.

34:21.790 --> 34:23.485
How do you do?
This is Ms. Watson, Mr. Holmes.

34:23.520 --> 34:25.078
They consult
for the department.

34:25.130 --> 34:26.154
They're the ones
who harassed Graham

34:26.190 --> 34:27.623
after the service
yesterday.

34:27.660 --> 34:29.855
We, uh, apologize
for any violation of decorum,

34:29.900 --> 34:31.697
but as it turns out,

34:31.730 --> 34:33.129
it was absolutely necessary.

34:33.170 --> 34:34.489
If we hadn't spoken,

34:34.540 --> 34:36.360
we may very well have
never learned the truth.

34:38.910 --> 34:42.402
You recognize that, right?

34:45.280 --> 34:47.339
It's my dad's.
Where'd you get that?

34:47.380 --> 34:48.711
It was hidden
in your father's office.

34:48.750 --> 34:51.389
You tried to take it out
of his desk last week,

34:51.420 --> 34:52.887
not Abigail.

34:52.920 --> 34:55.480
GREGSON:
Maybe you were thinking
about turning him in.

34:55.520 --> 34:57.659
Or maybe you were thinking
about stopping him

34:57.690 --> 34:59.487
from hurting your
little brother, too?

34:59.530 --> 35:01.157
What do you mean
"hurting"?

35:01.200 --> 35:03.498
Graham, what's he
talking about?

35:03.530 --> 35:05.259
Nothing.

35:05.300 --> 35:06.722
It's okay, Graham,
you can tell us the truth now.

35:06.770 --> 35:07.828
I don't understand.

35:07.870 --> 35:09.599
Are they saying that...?

35:09.640 --> 35:11.164
Are they saying

35:11.210 --> 35:12.165
your father...?
I don't want to talk...

35:12.210 --> 35:13.563
with you about this.

35:13.610 --> 35:15.339
Graham?
No!

35:15.380 --> 35:16.369
I want you to leave.

35:16.410 --> 35:17.377
Both of you, now.

35:17.410 --> 35:18.570
I can't allow
you to...

35:18.610 --> 35:19.577
I don't care!

35:19.610 --> 35:21.214
Just leave now!

35:21.250 --> 35:23.241
Mr. Delancey is 17.

35:23.280 --> 35:27.614
He is within his rights
to talk to us alone.

35:40.230 --> 35:41.492
(door closes)

35:41.540 --> 35:43.496
What's on there
doesn't prove anything.

35:43.540 --> 35:47.237
What it proves is that
your dad was a monster.

35:47.270 --> 35:49.636
And it certainly suggests

35:49.680 --> 35:51.807
that you have a very
understandable motive

35:51.850 --> 35:53.602
for wanting him dead.

35:53.650 --> 35:55.515
You knew about
Abigail's past.

35:55.550 --> 35:57.472
That's why you used
nitroglycerin.

35:57.520 --> 35:59.784
That's not true.

36:01.690 --> 36:04.386
This is a report prepared
for your stepmother

36:04.430 --> 36:05.749
by a private investigator
she'd hired

36:05.790 --> 36:07.781
to look into your father.

36:09.800 --> 36:11.267
These are your fingerprints.

36:13.500 --> 36:14.967
Abigail's whole story
is in that file.

36:15.000 --> 36:17.867
A story which
independently inspired you

36:17.900 --> 36:20.266
and your stepmother
to conceive

36:20.310 --> 36:22.369
the same plan.

36:22.410 --> 36:24.549
It seems that killing your
father and framing Abigail

36:24.580 --> 36:27.606
was an idea whose time had come.

36:27.650 --> 36:28.912
Hmm?

36:28.950 --> 36:31.384
Only you beat Peri
to the punch.

36:31.420 --> 36:34.287
You procured some nitroglycerin
illegally online,

36:34.320 --> 36:36.356
ifI had to guess.

36:36.390 --> 36:39.223
A few tablets in your father's
bourbon and...

36:39.260 --> 36:40.488
it was done.

36:40.530 --> 36:42.521
I doubt very much
that you relish

36:42.560 --> 36:45.267
what your plan means
for Abigail.

36:45.300 --> 36:46.699
But...

36:46.730 --> 36:49.631
compared to the hell
that your life had become?

36:49.670 --> 36:51.467
To the idea
that your secret would get out?

36:51.510 --> 36:54.604
To the idea that it could happen
all over again to Zack?

36:55.840 --> 36:56.807
It must've felt like

36:56.840 --> 36:58.376
you had little choice.

37:01.920 --> 37:05.549
Excuse me. I'm looking
for Graham Delancey.

37:05.590 --> 37:07.512
His little brother just
called me in tears,

37:07.550 --> 37:09.859
saying the police came
and took him away.
Yeah, Graham is in

37:09.890 --> 37:11.687
with the captain
right now.
Why?

37:11.730 --> 37:13.527
BELL:
I'm afraid I really
can't discuss...

37:13.560 --> 37:16.393
You. You saw Graham
almost every day.

37:16.430 --> 37:18.921
Did you have any idea
what was going on?

37:18.970 --> 37:20.426
Miss Moore, please.

37:20.470 --> 37:22.791
Wait, what are you
talking about?

37:22.840 --> 37:25.729
HOLMES:
I didn't mourn your father's
death, not for a moment.

37:25.770 --> 37:28.273
But Abigail loves you.

37:28.310 --> 37:30.938
Like you were one of her own.

37:30.980 --> 37:33.801
And I know
you care about her.

37:33.850 --> 37:36.341
If you stay silent,

37:36.380 --> 37:38.689
she'll go to prison.

37:38.720 --> 37:40.745
Does she really
deserve that

37:40.790 --> 37:42.485
for something
that she didn't do?

37:42.520 --> 37:44.852
WATSON:
Graham, you can help her.

37:46.030 --> 37:47.725
And we can help you.

37:47.760 --> 37:51.366
You just need
to tell us the truth.

37:51.400 --> 37:52.697
WHITMAN:
I need a few minutes

37:52.730 --> 37:55.039
alone with my
client. Now.

37:58.610 --> 37:59.861
(Gregson sighs)

37:59.910 --> 38:01.434
What the hell is going on?

38:01.480 --> 38:03.334
_ _ BELL: _
Abigail Spencer came in.

38:03.380 --> 38:06.042
She ran into Graham's aunt
and lawyer in the hall...

38:06.080 --> 38:08.640
And they told Abigail
about Graham's father.

38:08.680 --> 38:10.045
Next thing I
know, Abigail

38:10.080 --> 38:11.684
wants to make
a confe55ion.

38:11.720 --> 38:13.415
She says she's the one
who poisoned Titus Delancey.

38:13.450 --> 38:14.781
Crawford and Gleason

38:14.820 --> 38:16.583
are in interrogation
talking to her now.

38:16.620 --> 38:17.780
She say why she did it?

38:17.820 --> 38:19.378
According to her,

38:19.430 --> 38:21.057
_Titus uncovered her
real identity a few weeks ago.

38:21.090 --> 38:24.423
He was using it to try
to extort sexual favors.

38:28.970 --> 38:31.461
(sighs)

38:36.380 --> 38:38.701
(sighs heavily)

38:40.780 --> 38:44.409
The district attorney will not
pursue a case against Graham

38:44.450 --> 38:46.338
without a confession.

38:46.390 --> 38:48.017
Which he is unlikely to give us

38:48.050 --> 38:50.985
now that you have confessed
to killing his father.

38:53.060 --> 38:55.551
Why did you do it?

38:55.600 --> 38:58.023
Kill Titus?
I already explained that.

38:58.060 --> 39:00.961
No, why did you confess to
a murder that you didn't commit?

39:01.000 --> 39:02.968
I am a murderer.

39:03.000 --> 39:04.900
You said so yourself.

39:04.940 --> 39:06.498
You were right.

39:06.540 --> 39:09.429
Graham poisoned his father.

39:09.480 --> 39:11.948
You and I both know that.

39:13.980 --> 39:17.040
Graham is an amazing kid,

39:17.080 --> 39:19.878
and he has his whole life
ahead of him.

39:19.920 --> 39:22.718
He shouldn't be in prison.

39:22.760 --> 39:26.548
There's no doubt in my mind
that I did the right thing.

39:26.590 --> 39:28.899
By killing Titus Delancey.

39:28.930 --> 39:31.728
You know, you don't even need
to do this.

39:33.100 --> 39:35.568
We have proof
of what Titus did to Graham.

39:35.600 --> 39:37.989
He committed murder under
mitigating Circumstances.

39:39.910 --> 39:42.799
It's unlikely he will serve more
than 18 months.

39:42.840 --> 39:45.149
18 months.

39:46.510 --> 39:48.569
That's about the amount of time

39:48.620 --> 39:50.713
you and I wrote letters
to each other.

39:50.750 --> 39:54.550
Felt like a lifetime,
didn't it?

39:55.960 --> 39:57.450
Especially when you're branded

39:57.490 --> 39:59.788
the kid who killed your dad.

39:59.830 --> 40:02.048
And Graham deserves better
than that.

40:02.100 --> 40:04.762
(whispers):
You're innocent.

40:04.800 --> 40:06.529
No.

40:06.570 --> 40:08.435
Innocent?

40:08.470 --> 40:11.598
He was being brutalized
right in front of me,

40:11.640 --> 40:13.938
and I should have seen it,

40:13.970 --> 40:15.938
and I should have stopped it.

40:18.550 --> 40:20.871
Soonen

40:23.020 --> 40:25.716
Titus got what's coming to him.

40:25.750 --> 40:28.412
And now, so am I.

40:30.890 --> 40:34.087
Finally.

40:34.130 --> 40:36.655
(sighs)

40:41.600 --> 40:44.706
Thank you for agreeing
to speak with me.

40:44.740 --> 40:47.538
My school is near here.

40:47.570 --> 40:51.108
My aunt thought it was too soon
for me to go back, but...

40:51.140 --> 40:53.574
I don't know.

40:53.610 --> 40:55.475
I'm tired of being at home.

40:55.520 --> 40:59.809
Abigail's confession aside,
you and I both know the truth.

41:01.150 --> 41:03.880
I'm gonna be watching you.

41:03.920 --> 41:07.219
And if you resort to those...

41:07.260 --> 41:11.196
extreme tactics
again in the future,

41:15.870 --> 41:17.497
Is that clear?

41:22.980 --> 41:27.098
Have you spoken with anyone
about what happened to you?

41:28.880 --> 41:31.849
My Aunt Susan tried to ask me
some questions last night,

41:31.890 --> 41:34.211
but...

41:34.250 --> 41:37.014
It happened. It's over.

41:37.060 --> 41:38.857
Talking about it
won't change anything.

41:38.890 --> 41:41.654
You're wrong.

41:43.200 --> 41:45.566
I have never known a betrayal

41:45.600 --> 41:48.194
as—as profound as what
you've experienced.

41:49.640 --> 41:51.733
But I do know

41:51.770 --> 41:53.909
that being victimized is...

41:53.940 --> 41:56.238
is corrosive.

41:56.280 --> 41:59.977
And sometimes,
talking about it...

42:00.010 --> 42:03.070
that can help.

42:05.750 --> 42:08.082
So you ever want to...

42:08.120 --> 42:10.657
talk about it

42:10.690 --> 42:14.729
with someone who knows the story
in its entirety...

42:18.800 --> 42:20.859
...I'm at your disposal.

42:29.680 --> 42:32.001
*

